annotationA: S-adenosylmethionine synthase; Catalyzes the formation of S-adenosylmethionine from methionine and ATP. The reaction comprises two steps that are both catalyzed by the same enzyme: formation of S-adenosylmethionine (AdoMet) and triphosphate, and subsequent hydrolysis of the triphosphate
annotationB: Putative adenosylhomocysteinase 2; Adenosylhomocysteinase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: one-carbon metabolic process; Belongs to the adenosylhomocysteinase family
